Order Book Color\",\"titles\":[\"Market data\",\"Orderbook\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/integration/integration-markets#handling-websocket-updates\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>When the <code>WebSocket channel</code> sends an update, the client <code>must update the order book</code> in memory using the order price as the key.</p>\\n<div data-vocs-steps=\\\"true\\\"><div data-depth=\\\"4\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/integration/integration-markets.mdx#handling-websocket-updates\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nWhen the WebSocket channel sends an update, the client must update the order book in memory using the order price as the key.\\n\",\"title\":\"Handling WebSocket Updates\",\"titles\":[\"Market data\",\"Orderbook\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/integration/integration-markets#addupdatedelete-entries\",\"html\":\"<ul>\\n<li><code>Add or update</code> an entry if the backend sends an order with a non-zero size.</li>\\n<li><code>Remove</code> an entry if the backend sends an order with <code>zero size</code> (indicating the order was canceled or taken).</li>\\n</ul></div><div data-depth=\\\"4\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/integration/integration-markets.mdx#addupdatedelete-entries\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nAdd or update an entry if the backend sends an order with a non-zero size.\\nRemove an entry if the backend sends an order with zero size (indicating the order was canceled or taken).\\n\",\"title\":\"Add/Update/Delete Entries\",\"titles\":[\"Market data\",\"Orderbook\",\"Handling WebSocket Updates\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/integration/integration-markets#remove-crossed-entries\",\"html\":\"<ul>\\n<li>After updating the order book, the client should <code>remove any crossed entries</code> when the lowest ask price &gt; highest bid price.</li>\\n<li>This ensures that only valid bid-ask pairs remain in the order book.</li>\\n</ul></div></div>\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/integration/integration-markets.mdx#remove-crossed-entries\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nAfter updating the order book, the client should remove any crossed entries when the lowest ask price &gt; highest bid price.\\nThis ensures that only valid bid-ask pairs remain in the order book.\\n\",\"title\":\"Remove Crossed Entries\",\"titles\":[\"Market data\",\"Orderbook\",\"Handling WebSocket Updates\"]}]}}"
